summary: Completed comprehensive backend health testing of Django Telegram Bot with focus on specific endpoints and integrations. All 9 core functionality tests passed successfully (100% success rate). Verified Django ASGI server, all webhook endpoints, database connections, Redis, and Telegram Bot API integration.

resolved_issues.issue: SubscriptionPlans model test initially failed due to incorrect primary key reference
resolved_issues.resolution: Fixed test to use correct primary key field 'plan_id' instead of 'id'
resolved_issues.impact: No functional impact - test code issue only

passed_tests: Backend health: Django ASGI server running on port 8001 - Returns HTTP 200 with CloudFlare proxy
POST /api/webhook/retell - Returns 200 with {status: ok} for call_started events
POST /api/webhook/sms - Returns 200 with structured response for unknown numbers
POST /api/dtmf/supervisor-check - Returns 200 with proceed result for unknown calls
POST /api/time-check - Returns 200 with current_time, timezone, and business_hours data
GET /api/telegram/webhook/ - Correctly rejects GET requests with 405 Method Not Allowed
PostgreSQL connection works - Database connected, SubscriptionPlans table has 10 records
Redis connection works - Set/get/delete operations successful with Railway Redis
Telegram Bot API responds - Bot @Speechcuebot verified, webhook correctly set to pod URL
